article.description: — Mykel Derring scored a career-high 19 points and Jordan Minor tallied 11 points and 10 rebounds to lift Merrimack to a 62-51 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Thursday night.
article.headline: Minor carries Merrimack past Fairleigh Dickinson 62-51
article.linkText: Minor carries Merrimack past Fairleigh Dickinson 62-51
article.story: NORTH ANDOVER, Mass. -- — Mykel Derring scored a career-high 19 points and Jordan Minor tallied 11 points and 10 rebounds to lift Merrimack to a 62-51 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Thursday night. Mikey Watkins added 10 points for Merrimack (2-3, 2/3 Northeast Conference). .Ziggy Reid had seven rebounds. Brandon Powell had 15 points and seven rebounds for the Knights (2-7, 1-2). John Square Jr. added 11 points. The teams play again Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
